Definition: showing patient and unruffled self-control and restraint under adversity
Example: slow to retaliate or express resentment; seemly and forbearing...yet strong enough to resist aggression; was longanimous in the face of suffering
Synonyms: longanimous, noun, attribute, longanimity, showing, patient, and, unruffled, self-control, restraint, under, adversity, slow, to, retaliate, or, express, resentment, seemly, yet, strong, enough, resist, aggression, was, in, the, face, of, suffering
Category: adj.all
